  "body": "In-Class Exercises     There are many different, yet isomorphic, Boolean algebras with two elements. Describe one such Boolean algebra that is derived from a power set, , under . Describe a second that is described from , for some , under divides.  Since the elements of a two-element Boolean algebra must be the greatest and least elements, 1 and 0, the tables for the operations on are determined by the Boolean algebra laws. Write out the operation tables for .    Consider the Boolean algebra , and let be the set of bit strings of length six having an even number of 1's. Is closed with respect to the operations of .  Give an example of a Boolean algebra of order 16 whose elements are certain subsets of the set , the minimum element is the empty set, and the maximum element is .  Give an example of a Boolean algebra of order 16 whose elements are a certain set of bit strings of the set , whose minimum element is , and whose maximum element is .    "
