  "body": "In-Class Exercises    Suppose a two bit message is encoded into a five bit message using the function . What matrix, , has the property that ?  Define the two functions and by , and .  The values of and can be computed as matrix products. Determine the matrices.  Describe the function . Is it a homomorphism?     Suppose we were to send three bits across a binary symmetric channel by first encoding the bits using the function from the previous problem, producing a sequence of four bits. After receiving the four bits, the person at the receiving end applies the function to those bits. What can we derive from the output of ?  Linear Codes . Let and be positive integers. Suppose that is an matrix of zeros and ones. Then we can can define a function by where we take to be a matrix and we perform mod 2 arithmetic in computing the product . Prove that is a homomorphism.   "
